# Cloudflare Zero Trust root CA certificate.
# Required for the OpenCode container to make HTTPS connections to
# Access-protected origins (ai-sandbox.cloudemo.org MCP server).
#
# Obtain from: https://developers.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-one/connections/connect-devices/warp/install-cloudflare-cert/
# or from the Cloudflare Zero Trust dashboard: Settings → Resources → Download Certificate
#
# Replace this placeholder with the actual PEM certificate before building the container image.
# The certificate should look like:
#
# -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
# MIIDxDCCAqygAwIBAgIIBLBBpzpbREkwDQYJKoZIhvcNAQELBQAwgYsxCzAJBgNV
# ... (base64 encoded certificate data) ...
# -----END CERTIFICATE-----
#
# Without this certificate, the container will fail to connect to the MCP server
# with SSL verification errors when WARP is active.
-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
PLACEHOLDER_REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_CLOUDFLARE_ZERO_TRUST_CA_CERT
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
